# PHASE 1: DOMAIN UNDERSTANDING

## 1. What is AQI?

Air Quality Index (AQI) is a measure used to indicate the quality of air and its impact on human health. It converts pollutant concentrations into a single numerical value ranging from 0 to 500.

| AQI Range | Category     |
| --------- | ------------ |
| 0-50      | Good         |
| 51-100    | Satisfactory |
| 101-200   | Moderate     |
| 201-300   | Poor         |
| 301-400   | Very Poor    |
| 401-500   | Severe       |

---

## 2. Why Air Pollution Matters?

Air pollution affects both human health and the environment.

### Health Impacts

* Asthma
* Respiratory diseases
* Heart problems
* Eye irritation

### Environmental Impacts

* Smog
* Acid rain
* Climate change
* Reduced visibility

---

## 3. Major Pollutants

| Pollutant | Source                         | Health Impact      |
| --------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------ |
| PM2.5     | Vehicles, Industries           | Lung damage        |
| PM10      | Dust, Construction             | Respiratory issues |
| NO₂       | Vehicle emissions              | Asthma             |
| SO₂       | Coal plants                    | Breathing problems |
| CO        | Fuel combustion                | Oxygen deficiency  |
| O₃        | Chemical reactions in sunlight | Chest pain         |

---

## 4. Safe Limits

| Pollutant | Safe Limit |
| --------- | ---------- |
| PM2.5     | 60 µg/m³   |
| PM10      | 100 µg/m³  |
| NO₂       | 80 µg/m³   |
| SO₂       | 80 µg/m³   |
| CO        | 2 mg/m³    |
| O₃        | 100 µg/m³  |

---

## 5. How AQI Prediction Works?

AQI prediction uses historical pollution data, weather data, and machine learning models to forecast future air quality levels. In this project, XGBoost is used to predict AQI for the next 1 hour, 6 hours, and 24 hours.

## Conclusion

AQI monitoring and prediction help in identifying pollution trends and protecting public health. Understanding pollutants and their impacts is essential for building an effective Air Quality Prediction and Monitoring System.
